Package com.wordpress._0x10f8.logcheck.rule

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Rule
    Rule interface, defines that rules must have a name and the ability to evaluate a log file.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractRule
    Abstract rule, contains a useful method which maps a lambda function (or Matcher) to each line of a log, creating matches
    CompositeRule
    A composite rule is a rule which is made up of other rules.
    ContainsRule
    Check if a log entry contains a specific string
    RuleFactory
    Factory for generating Rule implementations parsed from JSON configuration files.
    SingleLineRegexRule
    Rule to match log file entries based on a regular expression mapped to a single log line.
    SurroundingMatchContainsRule
    A surrounding match contains rule looks at a specific log line, performs a regular expression group match on that line.
